article.headline: Phillips, Jennings help No. 10 Xavier to fifth straight victory
article.linkText: No. 10 Xavier goes on late run to seal victory
article.story:
OLEAN, N.Y. -- Ta'Shia Phillips and Special Jennings each scored 16 points to lead Xavier (No. 10 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) to a 62-53 win over St. Bonaventure on Saturday.

April Phillips added 12, and Amber Harris had 10 for the Musketeers (14-3, 4-0 Atlantic 10), winners of five straight.

The Bonnies drew even, 31-31, with 15:14 left in the second half after Armelia Horton hit both free throws, but Xavier went on a 10-2 run to seal the victory. Harris, the conference's third-leading scorer, had six of her 10 points in that stretch.

Dana Mitchell had 13 points, and Andrea Doneth added 10 for St. Bonaventure (14-6, 2-3), which has dropped three of four.

The Bonnies were held to 30 percent shooting from the field.
